						<summary>

						<p>This is a damaged inscription of <hi rend="bold">Jaṭāvarman Sundara-Pāṇḍya I</hi> with the Sanskrit introduction <hi rend="italic">Samasta jagadādhāra</hi> etc. (acc. A.D. 1251). It seems to register the gift of a village Maṇaṉūr (?) as <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> (probably by the king) for worship and repairs to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
